	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I could solo her with my level 47 cleric (probably could have at 44 when I bought my newest spells) easily enough, but you need to remember a few things. <BR>
<BR>
1) When you start walking towards her lair, pull the spiders out 1 at a time from a distance. I hit them with a lesser DD spell (like Wrath) to pull them to me, then finished each one off singly with my best DD (Retribution.)<BR>
<BR>
2) Once the spiders are clear, med up to full. You have lots of time before they repop. If you had to kill her PH, be sure it is the last one you kill so you can set up the spawn easier for when she does decide to show up.<BR>
<BR>
3) While she does hit really hard and fast, she also tends to resist spells like Root at the worst possible times. I am most successful when I pull her with Retribution, and just keep hitting her with it. Yes, she puts a beating on me. Pre-buffing is vital to your survival (All stackable AC/HP buffs including Symbol of X, as well as Resist Poison and Magic) will keep most toons up.<BR>
<BR>
5) If you are just to scared to play with her on her own turf, or get interrupted too often. Try this: bind at the zone, hit her with a root, then gate to the zone. You can sit down, med back up to full, and when you see the message that your root has worn off, stand up. She will run to you and (usually) not pull any others with her since she is so far away. (No, I dont understand aggro rules either, but it works.)<BR>
<BR>
Btw, Widdowmistress hair is for a quest in Paineel, and the resulting item is useable by Erudite Clerics only (you need the Eye of Urd from Lower Guk and the Lens of Lord Spotyvr from the Gorge of King Xorbb.)<BR>
<BR>
Yukiko Yamamoto, Vortex Flux, Lady of the Order of the White Rose
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
